# Releasing (wincher-mcp)

Releases use **git tags + GitHub releases** and **PyPI** (`wincher-mcp`). Prefer `scripts/publish_pypi.py` (see [publishing-version-to-pypi](../skills/publishing-version-to-pypi/SKILL.md)).

## Version alignment

| Artifact | Format |
|----------|--------|
| Git tag | `v0.1.0` (semver) |
| GitHub Release | Same tag title |
| Optional `CHANGELOG.md` section | `## [0.1.0] - YYYY-MM-DD` |

## Pre-release checks

```bash
python -m py_compile wincher_mcp_server.py
git status   # clean or only release files
```

Full workflow: [.cursor/skills/ship-release/SKILL.md](../skills/ship-release/SKILL.md).

## Hard rules

- **Never** tag or `gh release create` without explicit user approval for that version.
- **Never** force-push `main`.
- **Never** commit secrets in release notes or attached assets.

## Lineage

- Cherry-pick from `chris-tutt/wincher-mcp-server` only when needed; mention in release notes if you do.

## Red flags

| Stop | Why |
|------|-----|
| Release from dirty tree | Wrong artifact |
| Tag without compile check | Broken default branch |
| Force-push to fix a tag | History damage |
